cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on detecting cyber-attacks on in-vehicle networks and proposes a mechanism for the same.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges in adopting countermeasures proposed in the literature due to industry requirements and proposes a system-agnostic approach.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another likely category as the paper deals with the control systems of vehicles and proposes a mechanism for detecting deviations in the normal behavior of in-vehicle network dynamics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for detecting deviations in IVN traffic.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the communication patterns in in-vehicle networks.
